<Author>Andrew Bachmann
<Content>stark room, hard beds, crooked staff We got a good deal from a travel agent that recommended this hotel to us as a 4 star hotel. This hotel could barely rate a two star experience in my opinion.When we checked in I already had a bad feeling. The lobby is a small crowded hallway leading up to the elevators, which were probably the smallest elevators I have ever been in. Stepping out from the elevators into the skinny hallway didn't raise my expectations either. The hallway walls were bare. We entered our room and we were greeted with more of the same.The room was barely furnished with two beds, a cabinet, TV, and a refrigerator (which didn't seem to work). I turned on the TV and found out that the remote didn't work. (dead batteries?) There was one window in the room and it was frosted so you couldn't see out. (I felt like I didn't want to see what was on the other side anyway)The air conditioning was on full blast and even after turning it off the room was freezing. (even in the morning) The room also smelled strongly of an antiseptic odor.The bathroom didn't have any power outlets. The bathtub was really skinny and practically a hazard while taking a shower. There were wires connecting all the metal fixtures in the bathroom, for safety purposes. (weird)I sat down on the bed and it was like sitting on a desk. I've felt more comfortable sleeping on the ground outdoors than in this bed. The pillows were pretty sad too.They had wireless internet for 120 HKD for 24 hours, which I tried and was able to use. They charged us 5 HKD for local calls too, which surprised my girlfriend.After one night, we had enough so the next day we packed up early and checked out. We had paid in advance through the travel agent so we asked the hotel to refund the second night. (we had reserved two) The staff gave us the runaround. At first my girlfriend discussed the issue with them in cantonese. The agent at the hotel (who turned out to be the assistant manager !) claimed that the hotel wasn't in possession of the payment and was under a contractual obligation to charge for two nights. (The travel agent denied this) He also stated that he didn't want to refund the money to the travel agent because there would be no guarantees that the travel agent would refund the money to you. My girlfriend continued to talk to him and the agent while I went to check us into another hotel. When I finally came back 30-40 minutes later they were still going back and forth. We left to take our luggage to the other hotel.When we returned to the hotel I spoke to the same agent (in english). I explained to him that if he billed us for the night we didn't stay that I would call the hong kong tourist hotline and file a complaint. He eventually capitulated.We later found out that the hotel was in fact already in possession of the payment. After the hotel refunded the money to travel agent the agent returned the money to us nearly immediately.I tried to come up with some good things about this place and about the best I could come up with were: no bugs that we saw, there was hot water, and it seemed clean. (nothing to get dirty!) 
