<Content>Not recommendable! We stayed for three nights. Our room was surely not as nice as the one that is displayed in the internet. No reading lamps, much smaller and no light coming inside, because we faced the wall of a neighboring building.The matrasses and the bathroom were OK (room 1006) and if you are a single and just use it for sleeping it might serve your purpose, but if you are tired from walking through the city, you don't want to go back there, because it's no place to relax and feel comfortable. The TV reception was very poor, too.I agree with other reviewers about the unfriendly reception staff, although that's the thing you can cope with the easiest.Why I only rate it with one star is the cost performance ratio. It is far too expensive for what you get. I travelled through SE Asia and I'd say that for the same category you might pay 20USD (if ever) in Thailand, Malaysia or whatsoever. In Vietnam I had mere luxury for 15USD, but for the Imperial we paid 200 USD per night for a decent hole. Stay away! 
